File: Former Communication Minister Siphiwe Nyanda is suing former President Jacob Zuma for R800 000. JOHANNESBURG - Former Communication Minister Siphiwe Nyanda is suing former President Jacob Zuma for R800,000. Nyanda confirmed his lawyers have filed court papers against the former president. He claims Zuma defamed him by accusing him of being an apartheid spy. Zuma: Hanekom is a known 'enemy agent' ANC member Derek Hanekom is also suing Zuma for defamation for insinuating that he was a spy. He wants R500, 000 in compensation and an apology. Hanekom’s case was heard on Friday and judgment was reserved.